===Pronunciation===
Short i, normal l, hard k. Rhymes with [[milk]] and [[silk]].
===Noun===
Plural not in use (?).
# A Scottish [[clan]].
# Kind, sort, type, class of people, those that resemble (behave like, etc.) a certain person: "Rael and his ilk would have us believe that humans have been [[clone]]d." "Americans and their ilk are evil [[infidel]]s who must be destroyed!" "Adam and his ilk have caused problems at Wikipedia (though this stretches the meaning when there is only one person)." In this sense, ''ilk'' is almost always derogatory or humorously derogatory. (Derived from 1.)

